title: Fort Raleigh National Historic Site: Park Home
body: England's First Home in the New World  Fort Raleigh National Historic Site protects and preserves known portions of England's first New World settlements from 1584 to 1590.This site also preserves the cultural heritage of the Native Americans, European Americans and African Americans who have lived on Roanoke Island.              Exploring Fort Raleigh   Discover the different places to visit and learn about at Fort Raleigh National Historic Site
